WEBVTT

00:27.586 --> 00:35.076
Here at His Church, thanks for joining us online today as we spend intentional moments of worship, prayer, and digging into God's Word together.

00:35.597 --> 00:39.883
You know, we've come into this space, prayed up, ready to receive all that God has for us.

00:40.384 --> 00:44.589
In fact, we're starting a new conversation starting this week called Level Up.

00:45.050 --> 00:51.759
Really, that focuses on the foundations of our faith and how we can build upon that to receive all that God has for each of us.

00:52.640 --> 00:56.786
Now, to begin our time together today, we're gonna begin by singing a song

00:57.282 --> 00:58.344
called Welcome the Healer.

00:58.744 --> 01:06.356
And that song is really focused on welcoming the presence of Holy Spirit in our homes and our lives to receive all He has for us.

01:06.937 --> 01:10.643
So churches, we focus our time and attention on the Lord and worship.

01:10.663 --> 01:20.638
Let's proclaim His place of honor in our lives and thank and praise Him for His eternal promises, because we can expect God to intervene in our circumstances.

01:21.419 --> 01:25.746
God has actually promised to inhabit our worship and our praise, and He will.

01:25.922 --> 01:29.568
And when the king is present, all things are possible.

01:29.588 --> 01:34.816
I wanna read this scripture as we prepare our hearts and minds to encounter him today.

01:35.817 --> 01:39.202
Enter his gates with thanksgiving and his courts with praise.

01:39.703 --> 01:42.547
Give thanks to him and praise his name.

01:43.188 --> 01:47.274
For Yahweh is good and his love is eternal.

01:47.295 --> 01:51.381
His faithfulness endures through all generations.

01:52.583 --> 01:54.866
Church, let's welcome him in this place today.

01:55.170 --> 02:09.874
as we declare his praises.

10:29.570 --> 10:40.402
All of our future, the God who never fails, all of our faith in, all of our strength

17:47.842 --> 17:50.785
forever to the king of kings.

17:52.167 --> 18:00.035
You know, I'll never forget the moment where I asked Jesus to become my king of everything.

18:00.055 --> 18:06.942
I had gone through life and really allowed other people to determine where my life should go.

18:06.962 --> 18:09.986
And that left me feeling hurt and abused.

18:10.486 --> 18:15.812
And so I decided out of that, I'm not gonna let anyone influence my life.

18:16.433 --> 18:17.714
And so I took control over

18:18.082 --> 18:18.883
everything.

18:19.684 --> 18:29.294
And all that left me was a lot of fractured and broken relationships and me feeling just as depressed and lonely as I had before.

18:30.195 --> 18:38.384
So I just sat down at my high school library and I wrote out my prayer of surrender and salvation to Jesus.

18:40.066 --> 18:44.211
And from that moment on, things began to change.

18:44.671 --> 18:47.154
There were some things that changed overnight, like

18:47.394 --> 18:49.937
the sheer amount of weight that I just felt.

18:50.558 --> 18:57.105
But then there were other things that took longer to heal and to see restored, like the relationships in my life.

18:58.527 --> 19:10.060
But my point is this, that when we allow God to enter into our hearts and in our lives, we get to see spiritual transformation over time.

19:11.181 --> 19:15.826
And it's not just us alone that sees that transformation.

19:16.066 --> 19:26.642
We get to see changed lives in ourselves, in our home, and in our community, because there's ripple effects, because salvation changes everything.

19:28.945 --> 19:33.231
Would you pray with me as we go in today's sermon?

19:33.252 --> 19:43.026
Dear Lord, I just want to thank you and praise you for the fact that you sent Jesus to die for each and every single one of us.

19:43.202 --> 19:48.690
that you loved us that much, that you were willing to do that.

19:48.710 --> 20:02.288
God, I just pray that as we lean into today's sermon, that you would just open our hearts and our spirits and just speak something new and something fresh into our souls.

20:02.909 --> 20:07.155
God, you know exactly what each person needs to hear.

20:07.796 --> 20:12.402
So God, I pray that you would just be that whispering voice

20:12.738 --> 20:14.381
that they would know that it is you.

20:16.364 --> 20:30.067
So, God, I pray that as we go into today's message with Pastor Jeremiah speaking, that you would just be so tangibly present in our hearts, in our minds, and in our homes.

20:31.089 --> 20:33.333
Pray this all in your holy and precious name.

20:34.034 --> 20:36.338
Amen.

21:38.050 --> 21:40.072
Hey friends, good morning.

21:40.092 --> 21:43.635
It is so good to get to be with you today.

21:43.655 --> 21:52.983
I am so excited about what God has in store for us as we step into a whole new series of conversations that we're calling level up.

21:53.043 --> 22:08.036
It's an invitation for us to experience a next level in connection with God and with others and our purpose because we're really convinced that if we can each take some next steps in connecting more deeply

22:08.016 --> 22:11.781
God and one another in our purpose, it will change everything for us.

22:11.801 --> 22:31.409
So I want you to know that the heritage team has been praying for you today that this would be a series of conversations that changes us together, that moves us in a genuine sense and to a next level of connection with God and each other in our purpose.

22:31.469 --> 22:37.778
I can't wait to see how he does that as we just faithfully pursue him in moments like these.

22:37.890 --> 22:46.166
Now, as I've been preparing for this conversation, I was reminded of a story that some of you have heard me tell before.

22:46.727 --> 22:54.722
It's a story, actually, that was told to me one summer when I was helping take care of my thought the Pablo after he had surgery.

22:54.782 --> 22:56.946
So, thought that's a word that just kind of means grumpy.

22:57.090 --> 23:05.286
He had undergone some surgery and I never had had the chance to really hang out with him or get to know him very much.

23:05.506 --> 23:07.911
He was a very imposing figure in my life.

23:08.211 --> 23:13.682
I don't remember him smiling a whole lot and I remember him carrying around even as he aged.

23:13.826 --> 23:22.462
the hulk of a man who had spent his whole working life miles under the ground mining copper in the southeastern part of Arizona.

23:22.482 --> 23:23.143
That's what he had done.

23:23.164 --> 23:25.889
He had been a copper miner for his whole life.

23:26.129 --> 23:33.042
And one of the things about that, the Pablo, I wish you could meet him, is he did have a very dry sense of humor

23:33.090 --> 23:35.692
And he loved to tell tall tales.

23:36.033 --> 23:44.340
Now, with those two things combined, it was really tough for me to be able to figure out what was true and what wasn't when he would joke around with us.

23:44.360 --> 23:55.790
But on this particular day, that summer, as I was helping take care of him, he began to tell me a story that I really don't believe was one of his tall tales, but had a deep ring of truth to it.

23:55.830 --> 24:03.076
And I'm gonna share it with you here, because I think this story actually helps reveal to us some things about what God might say to us through his

24:03.056 --> 24:05.061
word here in just a moment.

24:05.081 --> 24:13.984
You see, Thata told me about one of the many times he had been buried alive as a minor in a mine collapse in southeastern Arizona.

24:14.425 --> 24:18.034
He told me about this particular experience, which still seemed to haunt him.

24:18.402 --> 24:35.984
And I kind of imagined myself in the spaces as the earth shook a little bit and then as handfuls and then shovelfuls and then bucketfuls and then torrents of cold earth and ore began to crash down around him and the men that he was with.

24:36.384 --> 24:44.274
He told me after that, which took forever, it seemed it started to get darker in the tunnel that he was in.

24:44.706 --> 24:52.438
You see, the cave-in had caused some of the overhead lights to go out, and then more, and then more, and then more.

24:52.498 --> 25:06.098
Until he said, all of the headlamps and shirt lights that the men with him were wearing had gone out, and he was left in the space that he told me he called the deep darkness.

25:08.902 --> 25:14.130
What do you do when you find yourself suddenly in deep

25:14.338 --> 25:14.879
darkness.

25:15.799 --> 25:20.444
What do you do when you find yourself crushed under the weight of all the earth it seems?

25:20.564 --> 25:23.427
And you are in now deep darkness.

25:23.487 --> 25:24.248
How do you get out?

25:24.288 --> 25:25.529
How do you find a way out?

25:25.549 --> 25:28.012
The truth is you don't because you can't.

25:28.432 --> 25:36.660
You need somebody else to act on your behalf, to open a way, to come from the outside in to that space of deep darkness.

25:38.442 --> 25:42.386
And I remember Thata expressing what that was like for him.

25:42.530 --> 26:07.442
And I wonder for you and for me how many of us today in this place would say that we are in a place of deep darkness, where it does feel as though we are carrying the weight of everyone's expectations, we're carrying the weight of our own concerns, we're in the darkness of separation between us and others, and though we are trying to get used to the darkness, it's not working.

26:07.746 --> 26:17.266
Because you see, one of the things with being in deep darkness is that we quickly move to understanding there's not a way out and the best we can hope for is to survive.

26:18.242 --> 26:29.537
And I think there are some of us in this conversation right now who are exhausted because we've been in a space in a place of just trying to make it, trying to survive.

26:29.738 --> 26:35.986
And we might not have articulated that we were in a place of deep darkness or separation, but that is where we have been.

26:36.267 --> 26:47.442
And what's fascinating and exciting to me is that the scriptures tell us of a God who saw us in our deep darkness, though he created us to be people of light.

26:47.618 --> 26:55.500
He saw us in the space where we had chosen willfully to move away from him into dark places and now found ourselves separated.

26:55.781 --> 27:03.442
And so he sent himself, he sent his son Jesus into our deep darkness as the bringer of light.

27:03.586 --> 27:08.714
This is in much kind of a thumbnail sketch, the story of scripture.

27:08.994 --> 27:16.766
But the truth of this and the hope of this is actually revealed in a passage we're gonna be looking at together today in the book of Colossians chapter one.

27:17.126 --> 27:20.191
I believe this is spoken to and for us here today.

27:20.792 --> 27:22.935
So Colossians chapter one, this is what the writer says.

27:22.975 --> 27:30.386
It says, God, He has enabled you to share in the inheritance that belongs to His people who live in the light.

27:30.818 --> 27:42.694
for he has rescued us from the kingdom of darkness and transferred us into the kingdom of his dear son who purchased our freedom and forgave our sins.

27:43.414 --> 27:51.345
And then the writer goes on to give us a picture of who Jesus is and how amazingly powerful and wonderful he is.

27:51.385 --> 27:53.067
And then he continues in verse 21.

27:53.768 --> 27:58.354
This includes you who were once far away from God.

27:58.530 --> 28:02.796
You were his enemies separated from him by your evil thoughts and actions.

28:03.617 --> 28:10.207
Yet now he has reconciled you to himself through the death of Christ in his physical body.

28:11.188 --> 28:16.535
As a result, he has brought you into his own presence.

28:16.556 --> 28:23.986
And you are holy and blameless as you stand before him without a single fault.

28:25.442 --> 28:36.392
I think there are some of us who are in this space where we are looking for a next level in connection with God or each other or our purpose.

28:36.733 --> 28:39.515
And the truth is it begins.

28:39.655 --> 28:45.621
In order to be able to find the next level, we kind of have to start at the basic level, which is simply this.

28:45.881 --> 28:50.025
It's that you and I are all in darkness and need of rescue.

28:50.045 --> 28:53.348
That it begins with the rescue of Jesus.

28:54.389 --> 28:55.250
Scripture says,

28:55.490 --> 29:04.624
is the one that God uses to move us from the kingdom of darkness into the kingdom of his son, who he loves so much.

29:04.984 --> 29:24.434
Jesus, by his work, because of what he has done, is the one who moves us from bondage into freedom, who moves us from the unforgivable into forgiveness, who moves us from being enemies of God to friends of his, who moves us from being separated by thoughts and actions to being reconciled.

29:24.514 --> 29:24.935
with God.

29:24.995 --> 29:27.218
This is who Jesus is.

29:28.479 --> 29:29.941
This is what he has come to do.

29:30.241 --> 29:42.818
This is kind of gut level, base level, honest with us when we find ourselves in the spaces of deep darkness to be aware that God is not okay with that.

29:43.178 --> 29:47.604
He hasn't left us to our own devices in the times and places of deep darkness.

29:48.485 --> 29:52.050
Instead, he has sent his son who he loves so much.

29:52.578 --> 29:57.465
So throughout this conversation today, we're actually gonna ask two questions.

29:57.765 --> 30:08.620
Two questions that if we can interact with them honestly, if we can listen to what Holy Spirit is telling us and then act on them, it will change everything.

30:08.660 --> 30:14.588
They will move us into our next level of connection with God and others in our purpose.

30:14.608 --> 30:15.669
I'm convinced of it.

30:16.350 --> 30:22.418
So the first question is this, where are you in deep darkness today?

30:23.234 --> 30:25.178
Like, let's just have an honest conversation.

30:25.458 --> 30:32.472
Let's just be gut level honest with the God of the universe who made us who is asking you, where are you in deep darkness?

30:32.512 --> 30:34.276
Your answer will not surprise him.

30:35.157 --> 30:39.666
He's pretty aware of where the deep dark spaces in your life are.

30:40.066 --> 30:41.247
He's not shocked by it.

30:41.548 --> 30:43.370
They don't cause him to love you any less.

30:43.710 --> 30:50.679
But I believe there's kind of just an initial conversation or question for us of where am I in deep darkness?

30:50.799 --> 30:55.925
Where am I feeling crushed under the weight of what has fallen on top of me?

30:56.225 --> 31:03.774
Where am I in the darkness of broken relationship, of depression or anxiety, of trying to figure it all out?

31:04.495 --> 31:06.898
Where am I in deep darkness?

31:09.026 --> 31:10.148
Where are you today?

31:11.409 --> 31:14.013
In this moment, where would you say, God?

31:14.033 --> 31:19.741
I need to be reminded that you see me in this space of deep darkness in my life.

31:19.761 --> 31:24.067
Scripture reminds us, one of his names is the God who sees.

31:25.830 --> 31:31.979
The one who sees us, even when it seems no one else can, because the darkness has closed in.

31:34.122 --> 31:37.106
Where are you in deep darkness today?

31:38.082 --> 31:58.232
As I mentioned earlier, each of us begin, in a sense, we start in a space where we because of the decisions of others, because of what we've inherited, because of our own words and actions, we find ourselves in the deep darkness of separation between God and us.

32:00.476 --> 32:07.346
And the invitation is to receive the rescue, the gift, the light of Jesus.

32:07.714 --> 32:11.860
to step into new life in Him, to receive what He offers.

32:12.121 --> 32:36.338
And so I'm actually gonna create some space right here, right now, for us, if we've not yet received the gift of rescue in Jesus, if we've not yet asked Him to be the one who forgives us, who rescues us, who moves us from darkness into life, and from darkness into light, and from death into life, if we've not yet asked Him to be our forgiver, our rescuer, our leader,

32:36.546 --> 32:39.189
then we're gonna create space to do that right now.

32:39.989 --> 32:46.056
So I just love, if that is you today, I'd like you to pray this prayer with me or one like it.

32:46.716 --> 33:01.051
And if it's prayed with honesty, if it's prayed as best as you know how, then understand this, that the result of that is you will have moved from the kingdom of darkness into the kingdom of his dear son who he loves so much.

33:01.811 --> 33:02.812
So let's pray this together.

33:03.733 --> 33:04.434
Jesus.

33:05.058 --> 33:09.042
I have been lost in deep darkness and need you to rescue me.

33:09.102 --> 33:12.405
I have done things I need your forgiveness of.

33:13.366 --> 33:17.430
I have lived in separation from you and I need you to reconcile us.

33:18.371 --> 33:23.395
You died and rose from the dead so I know you can do this in my life.

33:24.296 --> 33:28.881
I receive you as my rescuing savior and put my faith in you as my Lord.

33:29.801 --> 33:34.706
Help me to live for you in the light from this day forward.

33:35.010 --> 33:37.133
in your name, amen.

33:38.114 --> 33:42.381
If you prayed that prayer, you are, scripture says, a new creation.

33:42.401 --> 33:44.263
The prayer itself is not magic, right?

33:44.484 --> 33:45.846
They are not magic words.

33:46.146 --> 33:51.454
It's actually the posture of our heart and the request for Jesus to be the one who rescues us.

33:51.714 --> 33:54.578
Now, this is not something that we can go into alone.

33:54.818 --> 33:58.704
If you've just stepped into the relationship with Jesus, we want to journey with you.

33:58.724 --> 34:02.671
So I'm gonna ask you, if you did that, to let us know in a couple of ways.

34:03.232 --> 34:17.034
One, you can fill out a connect card, it's somewhere nearby you right now, you can use the church center app, but perhaps the most simple way is this, is simply to text the word light to 309-250-207.

34:17.795 --> 34:21.842
That's 309-250-

34:21.922 --> 34:32.416
2007, if you text the word light to that, you'll receive a response from us and a member of our pastoral team will follow up with you in a matter of days to help celebrate with you.

34:32.677 --> 34:37.904
You know, all of heaven just broke out in celebration that you entered into relationship with Jesus.

34:38.444 --> 34:45.554
And members of our team want to celebrate with you and help you continue on your journey to take these next steps.

34:46.210 --> 34:59.690
Some of us are trying to get to our next level of connection with God and others in our purpose, but we haven't yet taken this first step of receiving the gift of the one who has entered into our deep darkness.

35:00.732 --> 35:02.354
We've been trying to figure it out on our own.

35:02.735 --> 35:05.579
We've been trying to tunnel out on our own, and it's not working.

35:06.921 --> 35:07.622
It begins here.

35:09.124 --> 35:11.007
Don't let this moment pass you by.

35:12.309 --> 35:13.010
The reality is,

35:13.666 --> 35:21.033
The truth of the matter is our journey doesn't stop with us receiving the gift of light and life in Jesus.

35:21.574 --> 35:27.560
For some of us, we think that that is now the sum total of what must happen, of what needs to take place.

35:27.620 --> 35:35.208
That if we can just enter into relationship with Jesus, then everything else begins to open up for us and we don't have to do anything along the way.

35:36.229 --> 35:41.234
The reality is Jesus and his gift of rescue and salvation is a free gift we cannot earn.

35:41.314 --> 35:43.677
We don't have to do anything to convince God we deserve it.

35:44.718 --> 35:52.609
But when we have stepped out of the darkness into the light, we now must live as people of light.

35:53.810 --> 36:08.108
One of the problems, one of the challenges for us is for those of us who have been in the deep darkness so long, the light starts to feel wrong and incorrect and like it just doesn't belong because we've adapted so much to the space and place of darkness.

36:08.128 --> 36:09.330
We don't know what to do with the light.

36:10.210 --> 36:14.259
And so in fear or frustration or concern, we don't advance much further.

36:14.339 --> 36:22.859
But here's the reality that you and I are meant for a life that is full, that is adventurous, that has purpose and meaning.

36:23.120 --> 36:27.730
It begins, I am absolutely convinced, with receiving the rescue in light of Jesus.

36:28.098 --> 36:42.022
But then it's what we do once we have received that gift, how we chase after the good stuff of God knowing He loves us, that can really move us into next spaces of connection with God and others in our purpose.

36:42.342 --> 36:48.713
You see, it's really only just the beginning to receive light, because once it's received by us, we are to be vessels of light.

36:49.394 --> 36:53.842
Once we receive the rescue of Jesus, we are to be those who offer rescue.

36:54.562 --> 36:57.186
to act in rescue, to reveal his power.

36:57.586 --> 37:24.402
God's great plan, which astounds me, is that he desires to make his kingdom, his power, his light, his healing, his goodness, his truth, his mercy, his grace, his wonder, and his goodness known not through just supernatural acts, but to see you and I bring those things with us wherever we go.

37:24.962 --> 37:27.626
If you look at the scripture, you see this happen.

37:27.986 --> 37:36.338
Jesus first will say to his followers, hey, pray that the Lord send workers into the harvest field because the harvest is plentiful and the workers are few.

37:36.578 --> 37:41.365
So ask God to do a mighty harvesting thing and then in the same breath he says, and so now go.

37:42.186 --> 37:43.728
You just prayed for it, go do it.

37:43.988 --> 37:51.218
It's a picture for you and for me that the stuff of the miraculous that God wants to do in this world

37:51.298 --> 37:55.286
And what is more miraculous than seeing light come into darkness?

37:55.827 --> 38:04.585
The stuff of the miraculous that God wants to do in this world, He has chosen to do through us.

38:06.369 --> 38:07.391
This is exciting.

38:07.411 --> 38:08.754
This is good news.

38:09.858 --> 38:16.966
Some of us are stuck and stunted in our relationship with God and others in our purpose because we stopped at the moment in space of rescue.

38:17.266 --> 38:20.870
Our focus only on ourselves, on the light and rescue that we receive.

38:21.191 --> 38:25.836
And so we don't experience fullness or the next level of what God has for us.

38:26.096 --> 38:33.845
And we might in that space even find ourselves start drifting back into old patterns in ways of living.

38:35.266 --> 38:38.450
There's actually a passage of scripture that reveals this.

38:38.530 --> 38:39.231
starkly.

38:39.251 --> 38:42.334
It's a passage of scripture I don't like very much, actually.

38:42.754 --> 38:44.196
You'll see why here in a moment.

38:44.897 --> 38:49.221
It's one that if I can just be honest with you and really why can't I, right?

38:50.883 --> 38:52.244
It terrifies me a little bit.

38:56.188 --> 39:00.232
I don't know what to do with it all the time.

39:00.252 --> 39:05.618
Because as it speaks the truth of who we are meant to be, it shines a light on spaces in my own life.

39:06.658 --> 39:15.468
where I've chosen to retreat into what is known and safe instead of rescue for the sake of taking light, or instead of risking for taking light and rescue for others.

39:16.389 --> 39:20.334
This is what God says in Amos chapter five, through his prophet to his people.

39:21.395 --> 39:22.256
This is God speaking.

39:22.476 --> 39:25.419
I hate all your show and pretense.

39:26.400 --> 39:29.884
I hate the hypocrisy of your religious festivals and solemn assemblies.

39:30.305 --> 39:34.770
I will not accept your burnt offerings and your grain offerings.

39:34.882 --> 39:37.885
I won't even notice all your choice piece offerings.

39:38.606 --> 39:44.253
Away with your noisy hymns of praise, I will not listen to the music of your harps.

39:45.394 --> 39:45.955
Whoa.

39:47.276 --> 39:56.207
Instead, I want to see a mighty flood of justice, an endless river of righteous living.

39:57.729 --> 39:58.930
Here's the thing, friends.

40:00.322 --> 40:02.405
Throughout the scriptures, I have yet to find a space.

40:02.545 --> 40:04.888
It may be there, but I haven't found it yet.

40:05.209 --> 40:16.444
We do not see in the Bible God rejecting acts of worship or acts of justice, excuse me, because his people fail at worship.

40:16.464 --> 40:29.522
We do not see God rejecting acts of justice because his people fail at worship, but we do see him rejecting acts of worship because his people fail in the pursuit of justice.

40:35.458 --> 40:37.043
What are we to do with that?

40:37.343 --> 40:39.048
How are we to interact with us?

40:40.031 --> 40:47.272
It is an invitation, I believe, for me and for you to understand that justice is going into the darkness.

40:48.656 --> 40:50.802
Justice is seeking

40:50.882 --> 40:53.969
brightness when everything has gone wrong.

40:54.370 --> 41:02.387
It is moving in the power of Jesus as vessels of light and rescue where people are in deep darkness.

41:02.708 --> 41:06.476
And we address what is broken, what is hurting, what is vulnerable.

41:06.717 --> 41:10.866
We demand dignity and we work to see the goodness of God here and now.

41:10.914 --> 41:11.495
through us.

41:11.815 --> 41:15.641
We risk because God has risked everything for us.

41:16.101 --> 41:25.234
You see, the reality of salvation, of the rescue of Jesus, isn't just that we receive rescue and sit in it and hope everybody else might somehow find their way.

41:25.314 --> 41:33.586
But no, we then, as agents of rescue, as people of light, go where rescue and might are needed.

41:35.522 --> 41:47.274
